    "name": "COU1: Non-cannulated construct compression-bending prediction",
    "description": "FEA predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Validated by direct comparison to bench testing (N=11 constructs across two laboratories). Model influence MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence MEDIUM (pedicle screw fracture leads to revision surgery, not death).",
    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "decisionConsequence": "Medium",
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/applicability-constraint",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Applicability domain: non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw under quasi-static F1717 loading",
      "description": "The FEA model is applicable only to non-cannulated titanium-alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) pedicle screws with nominal outer diameter 7.5 mm ± 0.1 mm, thread pitch 2.75 mm, and overall length 45–55 mm, assembled with UHMWPE test blocks per ASTM F1717-15. The model is not applicable to cannulated variants, polyaxial head designs, or dynamic fatigue loading regimes. Screw-rod interface friction coefficient must lie within the characterized range (μ = 0.12–0.18). Predictions are valid only for the three QoIs explicitly validated: construct stiffness (N/mm), yield force (N), and force at 40 mm displacement (N)."
    },
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/operating-envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "Operating envelope: ASTM F1717 quasi-static compression-bending conditions",
      "description": "Loading: quasi-static compression-bending per ASTM F1717-15, crosshead displacement rate 5 mm/min ± 0.5 mm/min, maximum displacement 40 mm. Construct geometry: intervertebral body distance 50 mm ± 2 mm, rod diameter 5.5 mm CoCr. Temperature: ambient laboratory conditions 20–25 °C. UHMWPE block density 930–960 kg/m³. Applied compressive preload 100 N ± 10 N before bending ramp. FEA mesh element size 0.3–0.5 mm in screw-rod contact zone, global element size ≤ 1.0 mm. Material properties: Ti-6Al-4V E = 113.8 GPa ± 2 GPa, σ_y = 880 MPa ± 15 MPa."
    }
  },
  "hasSensitivityAnalysis": {
