    "name": "Global variance-based sensitivity analysis for non-cannulated pedicle screw FEA QoIs",
    "description": "A Sobol' variance-based global sensitivity analysis (N = 4096 quasi-random LHS samples) was conducted over eight uncertain input parameters — Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus (±2 GPa), yield strength (±15 MPa), isotropic hardening slope (±5 GPa), UHMWPE elastic modulus (±20 MPa), screw-rod friction coefficient (0.10–0.20), intervertebral distance (48–52 mm), rod diameter tolerance (±0.05 mm), and crosshead rate (4.5–5.5 mm/min) — revealing that Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus and screw-rod friction coefficient together account for 68% of the total output variance in construct stiffness, while yield strength dominates variance in yield force (first-order index S₁ = 0.54); crosshead rate and rod diameter tolerance contribute less than 3% each to all three QoIs, confirming that the mesh refinement and material characterization efforts are correctly prioritised.",
    "method": "Sobol variance-based global sensitivity (first- and total-order indices)",
    "dominantFactors": [
      "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus",
      "screw-rod friction coefficient",
      "Ti-6Al-4V yield strength"
    ],
    "sampleSize": 4096
  },
